This paper deals with optimizing prediction models using Random Forest, which is a popular machine learning algorithm used in various fields such as computer science, software engineering, artificial intelligence, and information retrieval. The paper specifically focuses on post-release defect prediction and web application effort estimation, which are sub-fields of software engineering and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
